    A discussion of issues is beyond the this paper.
    67 explain certain phenomena in discourse, we should be somewhat more explicit about the notions of center and realization.
    We have said that each utterance S in a discourse has associated with it a backward-looking center, Cb(S), and a set of forward-looking centers, Cf(S).
    What manner of objects are these centers?
    They are the sort of objects that can serve as the semantic interpretations of singular That is, either they are objects in the world (e.g., planets, people, numbers) or they are functions from possible worlds (situations, etc.) to objects in the world that can be used to interpret definite descriptions.
    That is, whatever serves to interpret a definite noun